    <h2>Malik's Story</h2>
    <p>Malik, a kind and hardworking 26-year-old African American man, was viciously attacked by a group of white men in a suspected hate crime. This racially charged assault left him with severe injuries — broken bones, facial fractures, and emotional trauma. He has undergone multiple surgeries and faces a long road to healing. </p>
    <p>Malik is more than a victim — he’s a son, a friend, a volunteer in his community. We are seeking $100,000 to cover his medical bills, trauma counseling, legal assistance, and the support he’ll need to rebuild his life.</p>
